  "texts": [
    "Ablation StudiesTo better understand the contribution of each component in DRaFT-Q, we conducted a series of ablation experiments.",
    "These ablations isolate the effects of core innovations in our method: dynamic rank allocation, reward-weighted optimization, and the mixed-precision 4/8-bit quantization.",
    "We also evaluate partial variants such as QLoRA augmented with reward-only loss and DRaFT-Q with dynamic-only updates to clarify the role of each enhancement.",
    "All ablations were performed using the Falcon-RW-1B model and evaluated across CommonsenseQA, OpenBookQA, and GSM8K.",
    "Dynamic Rank AllocationTo measure the importance of dynamic rank selection, we replaced the adaptive rank allocator with a static adapter rank of 8 across all layers, matching the configuration of standard LoRA and QLoRA."
  ],
